                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-26T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 26, 1929—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Your confidential telegram July 24, 10 p.m. Last paragraph. Department would
                    regard in a most serious light the export of laborers at this time when the
                    whole question of the export of labor is about to be made the subject of an
                    investigation. You may so advise President <pb facs="0410" n="292"
                        xml:id="pg_292"/> King informally suggesting the advisability of taking
                    steps to prevent any shipments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
